// Sample OpenSTA `report_checks` output for tiny_core (KOMPOSOS-V silicon STA fixture).
// Real OpenSTA/OpenROAD output parses with the same grammar; committed so sta.py is
// testable with no toolchain. One VIOLATED path (negative slack) and one MET path.

Startpoint: u_a3 (rising edge-triggered flip-flop clocked by clk)
Endpoint: u_a2 (rising edge-triggered flip-flop clocked by clk)
Path Group: clk
Path Type: max

   Delay     Time   Description
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
    0.00     0.00   clock clk (rise edge)
    0.00     0.00   clock network delay (ideal)
    0.00     0.00 ^ u_a3/CK (DFF_X1)
    0.18     0.18 ^ u_a3/Q (DFF_X1)
    0.22     0.40 v u_a1/A (INV_X1)
    0.09     0.49 ^ u_a1/ZN (INV_X1)
    0.16     0.65 ^ u_a2/B (NAND2_X1)
    0.00     0.65 ^ u_a2/D (DFF_X1)
             0.65   data arrival time

    1.00     1.00   clock clk (rise edge)
   -0.20     0.80   library setup time
             0.80   data required time
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
             0.80   data required time
            -0.65   data arrival time
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
            -0.15   slack (VIOLATED)


